@NODE "Short" "Short Description"
This prog fixes a little prob in the Karaoke MidiFiles from PC.
For some Kar files not recognized as Kar by midiplay
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Exemple" "Exemple French Kar File"
You know "Loosing my religion" the famous song from R.E.M. ?
For a long time I didn't can use it as a Karaoke file...Try it!

If you next run KaraoFIX on it, it will play perfectly (yes).
Why? What did KaraoFIX? It just had move a little sentence inside the file,
(generally for one char,but I had some with more..)
This famous sentence "MIDI KARAOKE FILE" that tell Midiplay it is a KAR.
Some KAR got some spaces (char$20) before, and Midiplay don't recognize
them. Why? Is it a bug? Is it a bad KAR file? I don't know.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "How to install it?"
Are you just stupid?
There are 2 files! the executable, and the exemple Kar file!
Put them where you want! let's go!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Use" "How to use it?"
This is just an amigados command!
so give it a file name to check....
Ex: KaraoFIX dh0:kars/LosingMyReligion.Kar
or ask him to scan a whole directory...
Ex: KaraoFIX dh0:kars/
ATTENTION! don't forget the final / or : otherwise it will try to scan a file

Don't hesitate to scan any directories...KaraoFIX is looking inside the files
before doing something... he knows recognize a Kar file and midifiles-only...
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Who" "Who shall use it?"
Everyone...what if there were some bad Kar files in your collection???
Come on! launch it on your dirs!
@ENDNODE

